Reliance Venture to Invest $150 Million by March 2012, PIT Says

-- B y   S i d d h a r t h   P h i l i p
-- 
2011-03-13T07:22:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-13/reliance-venture-to-invest-150-million-by-march-2012-pit-says.html
Billionaire  Anil Ambani ’s venture
capital arm, Reliance Venture Asset Management, plans to invest
$150 million in as many as 12 companies by March 2012, the Press
Trust of  India  reported, citing Harshal Shah, the fund’s chief
executive officer.  The fund is looking to invest in the defense industry as
well as in aerospace, health care and education, the report
quoted Shah as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Siddharth Philip in Mumbai at 
 sphillip3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Tighe at   ptighe@bloomberg.net . 